Class BlockingQueueConsumer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.util.AbstractService
      • org.threadly.concurrent.processing.BlockingQueueConsumer<T>
        • org.threadly.concurrent.BlockingQueueConsumer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of items contained in the queue to be consumed
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Service
    Deprecated. 
    See Poller.consumeQueue(java.util.Queue, java.util.function.Consumer) or BlockingQueueConsumer for replacement

    @Deprecated
public class BlockingQueueConsumer<T>
extends BlockingQueueConsumer<T>
    Migration off this deprecated implementation is highly encouraged. Javadocs removed in 5.37 in replacement for BlockingQueueConsumer. This class slipped under the radar, causing the implementation and interface to be significantly behind in threadly 5.X. Please switch to Poller.consumeQueue(java.util.Queue, java.util.function.Consumer) or BlockingQueueConsumer.
    Since:
    1.0.0
